 72            int diff = (int)(tick - firstTick);
 73            /* If the difference is larger than replicatesCount
 74             * then that means the replicates collection is missing

 448        /// <summary>

 0470            if (anyChanged)
 0471            {
 0472                _lastTransformPosition = transform.position;
 0473                _lastTransformRotation = transform.rotation;
 0474                _lastTransformScale = transform.localScale;

 693            void ReplicateData(ReplicateDataContainer<T> data, ReplicateState state)
 0694            {
 0695                uint tick = data.Data.GetTick();
 696#if !FISHNET_STABLE_REPLICATESTATES
 0697                SetReplicateTick(tick, state.ContainsCreated());
 698#else
 699                SetReplicateTick(tick, (state == ReplicateState.CurrentCreated));
 700#endif
 701                /* If server or appended state order then insert/add to history when run
 702                 * within this method.
 703                 * Whether data is inserted/added into the past (replicatesHistory) depends on
 704                 * if client only && and state order.
 705                 *
 706                 * Server only adds onto the history after running the inputs. This is so
 707                 * the server can send past inputs with redundancy.
 708                 *
 709                 * Client inserts into the history under two scenarios:
 710                 *  - If state order is using inserted. This is done when the data is read so it
 711                 *  can be iterated during the next reconcile, since the data is not added to
 712                 *  a queue otherwise. This is what causes the requirement to reconcile to run
 713                 *  datas.
 714                 *  - If the state order if using append, and the state just ran. This is so that
 715                 *  the reconcile does not replay data which hasn't yet run. But, the data should still
 716                 *  be inserted at point of run so reconciles can correct to the state at the right
 717                 *  point in history.*/
 718
 719                //Server always adds.
 0720                if (isServer)
 0721                    AddReplicatesHistory(replicatesHistory, data);
 722                //If client insert value into history.
 723                else
 0724                    InsertIntoReplicateHistory(data, replicatesHistory);
 725
 0726                del.Invoke(data.Data, state, data.Channel);
 0727            }

 0776                state = (ReplicateState.Replayed | ReplicateState.Ticked | ReplicateState.Created);
 777#else
 778                state = ReplicateState.ReplayedCreated;
 779#endif
 780
 781                //SetReplicateTick(data.GetTick(), true);
 0782                del.Invoke(dataContainer.Data, state, dataContainer.Channel);
 0783            }
 0784        }

 786        /// <summary>
 787        /// Replays an input for non authoritative entity.
 788        /// </summary>
 789        [MakePublic]
 790        private void Replicate_Replay_NonAuthoritative<T>(uint replayTick, ReplicateUserLogicDelegate<T> del, RingBuffer
 0791        {
 792            //NOTESSTART
 793            /* When inserting states only replay the first state after the reconcile.
 794             * This prevents an inconsistency on running created states if other created states
 795             * were to arrive late. Essentially the first state is considered 'current' and the rest
 796             * are acting as a buffer against unsteady networking conditions. */
 797
 798            /* When appending states all created can be run. Appended states are only inserted after they've
 799             * run at the end of the tick, which performs of it's own queue. Because of this, it's safe to assume
 800             * if the state has been inserted into the past it has already passed it's buffer checks. */
 801            //NOTESEND
 802            ReplicateDataContainer<T> dataContainer;
 803            ReplicateState state;
 0804            bool isAppendedOrder = _networkObjectCache.PredictionManager.IsAppendedStateOrder;
 805            //If the first replay.
 0806            if (isAppendedOrder || replayTick == (_networkObjectCache.PredictionManager.ServerStateTick + 1))
 0807            {
 808                ReplicateTickFinder.DataPlacementResult findResult;
 0809                int replicateIndex = ReplicateTickFinder.GetReplicateHistoryIndex(replayTick, replicatesHistory, out fin
 810                //If not found then something went wrong.
 0811                if (findResult == ReplicateTickFinder.DataPlacementResult.Exact)
 0812                {
 0813                    dataContainer = replicatesHistory[replicateIndex];
 814
 815#if !FISHNET_STABLE_REPLICATESTATES
 0816                    state = ReplicateState.Replayed;
 817
 0818                    bool isCreated = dataContainer.IsCreated;
 819                    //Set if created.
 0820                    if (isCreated)
 0821                        state |= ReplicateState.Created;
 822                    /* Ticked will be true if value had ticked outside of reconcile,
 823                     * or if data is created. It's possible for data to be created
 824                     * and not yet ticked if state order is inserted rather than append. */
 0825                    if (replayTick <= _lastOrderedReplicatedTick || isCreated)
 0826                        state |= ReplicateState.Ticked;
 827#else
 828                    //state = ReplicateState.ReplayedCreated;
 829                    state = (dataContainer.IsCreated) ? ReplicateState.ReplayedCreated : ReplicateState.ReplayedFuture;
 830#endif
 0831                }
 832                else
 0833                {
 0834                    SetDataToDefault();
 0835                }
 0836            }
 837            //Not the first replay tick.
 838            else
 0839            {
 0840                SetDataToDefault();
 0841            }
 842
 843            void SetDataToDefault()
 0844            {
 0845                dataContainer = ReplicateDataContainer<T>.GetDefault(replayTick);
 846#if !FISHNET_STABLE_REPLICATESTATES
 0847                state = ReplicateState.Replayed;
 848#else
 849                state = ReplicateState.ReplayedFuture;
 850#endif
 0851            }
 852
 0853            del.Invoke(dataContainer.Data, state, dataContainer.Channel);
 0854        }

 874        /// <summary>
 875        /// Returns the DeltaSerializeOption to use for the tick.
 876        /// </summary>
 877        /// <param name="resendsEnded"></param>
 878        /// <returns></returns>
 879        private DeltaSerializerOption GetDeltaSerializeOption()
 0880        {
 0881            uint localTick = _networkObjectCache.TimeManager.LocalTick;
 0882            ushort tickRate = _networkObjectCache.TimeManager.TickRate;
 883            /* New observers so send a full serialize next replicate.
 884             * This could go out to only the newly added observers, but it
 885             * would generate a lot more complexity to save presumably
 886             * a small amount of occasional bandwidth. */
 0887            if (_networkObjectCache.ObserverAddedTick == localTick)
 0888                return DeltaSerializerOption.FullSerialize;
 889            //Send full every half a second.
 890            //else if (localTick % tickRate == 0 || localTick % (tickRate / 2) == 0)
 891            //     return DeltaSerializerOption.FullSerialize;
 892            //Send full every second.
 0893            else if (localTick % tickRate == 0)
 0894                return DeltaSerializerOption.FullSerialize;
 895            //Otherwise return rootSerialize, the default for sending the child most data.
 896            else
 0897                return DeltaSerializerOption.RootSerialize;
 0898        }

 900        /// <summary>
 901        /// Sends a Replicate to server or clients.

 903        private void Replicate_SendAuthoritative<T>(bool toServer, uint hash, int pastInputs, RingBuffer<ReplicateDataCo
 0904        {
 905            /* Do not use IsSpawnedWithWarning because the server
 906             * will still call this a tick or two as clientHost when
 907             * an owner disconnects. This comes from calling Replicate(default)
 908             * for the server-side processing in NetworkBehaviours. */
 0909            if (!IsSpawned)
 0910                return;
 911
 0912            int historyCount = replicatesHistory.Count;
 913            //Nothing to send; should never be possible.
 0914            if (historyCount <= 0)
 0915                return;

 917            //Number of past inputs to send.
 0918            if (historyCount < pastInputs)
 0919                pastInputs = historyCount;
 920            /* Where to start writing from. When passed
 921             * into the writer values from this offset
 922             * and forward will be written.
 923             * Always write up to past inputs. */
 0924            int offset = (historyCount - pastInputs);
 925
 926            //Write history to methodWriter.
 0927            PooledWriter methodWriter = WriterPool.Retrieve(WriterPool.LENGTH_BRACKET);
 928            /* If going to clients from the server then
 929             * write the queueTick. */

 0931                methodWriter.WriteTickUnpacked(queuedTick);
 932//#if !FISHNET_STABLE_SYNCTYPES

 934            methodWriter.WriteDeltaReplicate(replicatesHistory, offset, deltaOption);
 935#else

 940

 942             * When clientHost and here replicates will
 943             * always just send to clients, while
 944             * excluding clientHost. */
 0945            if (toServer)
 0946            {
 0947                NetworkManager.TransportManager.SendToServer((byte)channel, writer.GetArraySegment(), splitLargeMessages
 0948            }
 949            else
 0950            {
 951                /* If going to clients from server, then only send
 952                 * if state forwarding is enabled. */
 0953                if (_networkObjectCache.EnableStateForwarding)
 0954                {
 955                    //Exclude owner and if clientHost, also localClient.
 0956                    _networkConnectionCache.Clear();
 0957                    _networkConnectionCache.Add(Owner);
 0958                    if (IsClientStarted)
 0959                        _networkConnectionCache.Add(ClientManager.Connection);

 0961                    NetworkManager.TransportManager.SendToClients((byte)channel, writer.GetArraySegment(), Observers, _n
 0962                }
 0963            }

 965            /* If sending as reliable there is no reason
 966             * to perform resends, so clear remaining resends. */
 0967            if (channel == Channel.Reliable)
 0968                _remainingReplicateResends = 0;
 969
 0970            methodWriter.StoreLength();
 0971            writer.StoreLength();
 0972        }

 974        /// <summary>
 975        /// Reads a replicate the client.
 976        /// </summary>
 977        [MakePublic]
 978        internal void Replicate_Reader<T>(uint hash, PooledReader reader, NetworkConnection sender, ref ReplicateDataCon
 0979        {
 980            /* This will never be received on owner, except in the condition
 981             * the server is the owner and also a client. In such condition
 982             * the method is exited after data is parsed. */
 0983            PredictionManager pm = _networkObjectCache.PredictionManager;
 0984            TimeManager tm = _networkObjectCache.TimeManager;
 0985            bool fromServer = (reader.Source == Reader.DataSource.Server);
 986
 987            uint tick;
 988            /* If coming from the server then read the tick. Server sends tick
 989             * if authority or if relaying from another client. The tick which
 990             * arrives will be the tick the replicate will run on the server. */
 0991            if (fromServer)
 0992                tick = reader.ReadTickUnpacked();
 993            /* When coming from a client it will always be owner.
 994             * Client sends out replicates soon as they are run.
 995             * It's safe to use the LastRemoteTick from the client
 996             * in addition to QueuedInputs. */
 997            else
 0998                tick = (tm.LastPacketTick.LastRemoteTick);
 999
 1000//#if !FISHNET_STABLE_SYNCTYPES
 1001#if DO_NOT_USE
 1002            receivedReplicatesCount = reader.ReadDeltaReplicate(lastReadReplicate, ref arrBuffer, tick);
 1003#else
 01004            List<ReplicateDataContainer<T>> readReplicates = reader.ReadReplicate<T>(tick);
 1005#endif
 1006            //Update first read if able.
 01007            if (readReplicates.Count > 0)
 01008            {
 01009                lastReadReplicate.Dispose();
 01010                lastReadReplicate = readReplicates[^1];
 01011            }
 1012
 1013            //If received on clientHost simply ignore after parsing data.
 01014            if (fromServer && IsHostStarted)
 01015                return;
 1016
 1017            /* Replicate rpc readers relay to this method and
 1018             * do not have an owner check in the generated code.
 1019             * Only server needs to check for owners. Clients
 1020             * should accept the servers data regardless.
 1021             *
 1022             * If coming from a client and that client is not owner then exit. */
 01023            if (!fromServer && !OwnerMatches(sender))
 01024                return;
 1025            //Early exit if old data.
 01026            if (TimeManager.LastPacketTick.LastRemoteTick < _lastReplicateReadRemoteTick)
 01027                return;
 01028            _lastReplicateReadRemoteTick = TimeManager.LastPacketTick.LastRemoteTick;
 1029
 1030            //If from a client that is not clientHost do some safety checks.
 01031            if (!fromServer && !Owner.IsLocalClient)
 01032            {
 01033                if (readReplicates.Count > pm.RedundancyCount)
 01034                {
 01035                    sender.Kick(reader, KickReason.ExploitAttempt, LoggingType.Common, $"Connection {sender.ToString()} 
 01036                    return;
 1037                }
 01038            }
 1039
 01040            Replicate_EnqueueReceivedReplicate(readReplicates, replicatesQueue, replicatesHistory);
 01041            Replicate_SendNonAuthoritative(hash, replicatesQueue, channel);
 1042
 01043            CollectionCaches<ReplicateDataContainer<T>>.Store(readReplicates);
 01044        }
 1045
 1046        /// <summary>
 1047        /// Sends data from a reader which only contains the replicate packet.
 1048        /// </summary>
 1049        [MakePublic]
 1050        internal void Replicate_SendNonAuthoritative<T>(uint hash, BasicQueue<ReplicateDataContainer<T>> replicatesQueue
 01051        {
 01052            if (!IsServerStarted)
 01053                return;
 01054            if (!_networkObjectCache.EnableStateForwarding)
 01055                return;
 1056
 01057            int queueCount = replicatesQueue.Count;
 1058            //None to send.
 01059            if (queueCount == 0)
 01060                return;
 1061
 1062            //If the only observer is the owner then there is no need to write.
 01063            int observersCount = Observers.Count;
 1064            //Quick exit for no observers other than owner.
 01065            if (observersCount == 0 || (Owner.IsValid && observersCount == 1))
 01066                return;
 1067
 01068            PooledWriter methodWriter = WriterPool.Retrieve(WriterPool.LENGTH_BRACKET);
 1069
 01070            uint localTick = _networkObjectCache.TimeManager.LocalTick;
 1071            /* Write when the last entry will run.
 1072             *
 1073             * Typically, the last entry will run on localTick + (queueCount - 1).
 1074             * 1 is subtracted from queueCount because in most cases the first entry
 1075             * is going to run same tick.
 1076             * An exception is when the replicateStartTick is set, then there is going
 1077             * to be a delayed based on start tick difference. */
 01078            uint runTickOflastEntry = localTick + ((uint)queueCount - 1);
 1079            //If start tick is set then add on the delay.
 01080            if (_replicateStartTick != TimeManager.UNSET_TICK)
 01081                runTickOflastEntry += (_replicateStartTick - TimeManager.LocalTick);
 1082            //Write the run tick now.
 01083            methodWriter.WriteTickUnpacked(runTickOflastEntry);
 1084            //Write the replicates.
 01085            int redundancyCount = (int)Mathf.Min(_networkObjectCache.PredictionManager.RedundancyCount, queueCount);
 1086//#if !FISHNET_STABLE_SYNCTYPES
 1087#if DO_NOT_USE
 1088            methodWriter.WriteDeltaReplicate(replicatesQueue, redundancyCount, GetDeltaSerializeOption());
 1089#else
 01090            methodWriter.WriteReplicate<T>(replicatesQueue, redundancyCount);
 1091#endif
 01092            PooledWriter writer = CreateRpc(hash, methodWriter, PacketId.Replicate, channel);
 1093
 1094            //Exclude owner and if clientHost, also localClient.
 01095            _networkConnectionCache.Clear();
 01096            if (Owner.IsValid)
 01097                _networkConnectionCache.Add(Owner);
 01098            if (IsClientStarted && !Owner.IsLocalClient)
 01099                _networkConnectionCache.Add(ClientManager.Connection);
 1100
 01101            NetworkManager.TransportManager.SendToClients((byte)channel, writer.GetArraySegment(), Observers, _networkCo
 1102
 01103            methodWriter.StoreLength();
 01104            writer.StoreLength();
 01105        }

 1107        /// <summary>
 1108        /// Handles a received replicate packet.
 1109        /// </summary>
 1110        private void Replicate_EnqueueReceivedReplicate<T>(List<ReplicateDataContainer<T>> readDatas, BasicQueue<Replica
 01111        {
 01112            int startQueueCount = replicatesQueue.Count;
 1113            /* Owner never gets this for their own object so
 1114             * this can be processed under the assumption data is only
 1115             * handled on unowned objects. */
 01116            PredictionManager pm = PredictionManager;
 1117
 01118            bool isServer = _networkObjectCache.IsServerStarted;
 01119            bool isAppendedOrder = pm.IsAppendedStateOrder;
 1120
 1121            //Maximum number of replicates allowed to be queued at once.
 01122            int maximmumReplicates = (IsServerStarted) ? pm.GetMaximumServerReplicates() : pm.MaximumPastReplicates;
 1123
 01124            for (int i = 0; i < readDatas.Count; i++)
 01125            {
 01126                ReplicateDataContainer<T> dataContainer = readDatas[i];
 01127                dataContainer.IsCreated = true;
 01128                uint tick = dataContainer.Data.GetTick();
 1129
 1130                //Skip if old data.
 01131                if (tick <= _lastReadReplicateTick)
 01132                {
 01133                    dataContainer.Dispose();
 01134                    continue;
 1135                }
 1136
 01137                _lastReadReplicateTick = tick;
 1138
 1139                //Cannot queue anymore, discard oldest.
 01140                if (replicatesQueue.Count > maximmumReplicates)
 01141                {
 01142                    ReplicateDataContainer<T> disposableDataContainer = replicatesQueue.Dequeue();
 01143                    disposableDataContainer.Dispose();
 01144                }
 1145
 1146                /* Check if replicate is already in history.
 1147                 * This can occur when the replicate method has a predicted
 1148                 * state for the tick, but a user created replicate comes
 1149                 * through afterward.
 1150                 *
 1151                 * Only perform this check if not the server, since server
 1152                 * does not reconcile it will never use replicatesHistory.
 1153                 *
 1154                 * When clients are also using ReplicateStateOrder.Future the replicates
 1155                 * do not need to be put into the past, as they're always added onto
 1156                 * the end of the queue.
 1157                 *
 1158                 * The server also does not predict replicates in the same way
 1159                 * a client does. When an owner sends a replicate to the server
 1160                 * the server only uses the owner tick to check if it's an old replicate.
 1161                 * But when running the replicate, the server applies it's local tick and
 1162                 * sends that to spectators. */
 1163                //Add automatically if server or future order.
 01164                if (isServer || isAppendedOrder)
 01165                    replicatesQueue.Enqueue(dataContainer);
 1166                //Run checks to replace data if not server.
 1167                else
 01168                    InsertIntoReplicateHistory(dataContainer, replicatesHistory);
 01169            }
 1170
 1171            /* If entries are being added after nothing then
 1172             * start the queued inputs delay. Only the server needs
 1173             * to do this since clients implement the queue delay
 1174             * by holding reconcile x ticks rather than not running received
 1175             * x ticks. */
 01176            if ((isServer || isAppendedOrder) && startQueueCount == 0 && replicatesQueue.Count > 0)
 01177                _replicateStartTick = (_networkObjectCache.TimeManager.LocalTick + pm.StateInterpolation);
 01178        }
 1179
 1180        /// <summary>
 1181        /// Inserts data into the replicatesHistory collection.
 1182        /// This should only be called when client only.
 1183        /// </summary>
